      "summary": "The discussion centered on significant technical achievements with ElizaOS. zadayos successfully booted ElizaOS Debian RISC-V 64-bit ISO on QEMU chip emulator in 35 seconds, demonstrating cross-architecture compatibility. shawmakesmagic confirmed Eliza v3 is running on elizaOS (Linux) on an emulated RISC-V chip called 'eliza e1', representing a major milestone in hardware abstraction. When asked about custom chip development, the question about a physical Eliza E1 chip remained unanswered. On the business side, shawmakesmagic clarified that the previously mentioned Babylon airdrop for elizaos holders will not happen due to budget constraints, with the team now focusing exclusively on elizaOS development. This strategic pivot was strongly supported by zadayos, who advocated for single-token focus similar to ETH/SOL utility models, leaving ecosystem token creation to the market. Regarding Milady token buyback, odilitime confirmed it's the BNB version. janabr8973 announced a new DeFi plugin for Eliza on Base/Aave, offering real-time solvency scoring and flash-crash simulations via NPM package @centinel-risk-protocol/eliza-plugin-centinel, seeking community testing and feedback.",
